  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: on release 0.13.0 all uppercase was replaced by lowercase in recovery phrase input field automatically. Now on Android recovery phrase with capital letters remains the same, but anyway it recovers right account (whisper id + wallet address)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nrecovery phrase in lowercase\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nrecovery phrase is persisted\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Tap on \"Access key\"\r\n- Enter phrase with uppercase letters\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n- Status version: nightly 21/08/2019\r\n- Operating System: Android\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\nVideo and logs: https://app.saucelabs.com/tests/1d8650491fd7488b8dacdf85c7707c4d?auth=6b244604bc292931a211ca12523a9b24v",
